URL: https://sachsmc.github.io/xactonomial/
BugReports: https://github.com/sachsmc/xactonomial/issues/
Description: We consider the problem where we observe k vectors
    (possibly of different lengths), each representing an independent 
    multinomial random vector. For a given function psi which takes in the concatenated
    vector of multinomial probabilities and outputs a real number, this is a 
    Monte Carlo estimation procedure of an exact p-value and confidence interval.
    The resulting inference is valid even in small samples, and when the parameter is 
    on the boundary, and when the function is nondifferentiable at the parameter value, 
    all situations where asymptotic methods and the bootstrap would fail. 
